        public static boolean isInsideDateInterval(java.time.LocalDateTime dateToTest,

                                           boolean endIncluded)

        Parameters:
        dateToTest - the date to test
        startIntervalDate - the lower boundary of the date interval
        startIncluded - is the lower boundary included?
        endIntervalDate - the upper boundary of the date interval
        endIncluded - is the upper boundary included?
        Returns:
        true if dateToTest is inside |startIntervalDate ; endIntervalDate| (the sense of the brackets depends of the booleans) ; else false.

      • isInsideHourInterval

        public static boolean isInsideHourInterval(java.time.LocalDateTime timeToTest,
                                           java.time.LocalTime startIntervalHour,
                                           java.time.LocalTime endIntervalHour)
        Check whether the hour of hourToTest is inside the interval defined by [startIntervalHour ; endIntervalHour]. In this test, only the hours and minutes are considered (seconds, milliseconds, ... are ignored).
        Parameters:
        timeToTest - the hour to test
        startIntervalHour - the lower boundary of the hour interval
        endIntervalHour - the upper boundary of the hour interval
        Returns:
        true if the time (Hours Minutes) of hourToTest is inside [startIntervalHour ; endIntervalHour] ; else false.
